# 3DAIGC-API + Character Studio Workflow

## Where things run

- **DGX Spark**: `3DAIGC-API` backend (`/home/sifr/3DAIGC-API`, port `7842`)
- **PC**: Character Studio dev server (`/home/sifr/OpenNexus3DStudio`, Vite)

Do **not** start the Character Studio dev server on Spark unless the user explicitly asks. The user runs it locally on their PC.

## Complementary changes (required)

Backend and frontend are one integration. When changing `3DAIGC-API`, also update Character Studio so the client matches the API contract.

| Backend change | Character Studio counterpart |
|----------------|------------------------------|
| New model in `config/models.yaml` + adapter | `src/library/aiModelsCatalog.js` (model entry, labels, defaults) |
| API request/response shape | `src/library/taskManager.js` (upload flow, payloads, polling) |
| Model params / `output_format` | `src/components/TaskAdvancedOptions.jsx`, catalog defaults |
| Feature availability | Dynamic model lists from `/api/v1/system/models` — avoid hardcoded dropdowns |

Reference API docs: `Open3DStudio/docs/api/api.md` and `3DAIGC-API/docs/api_documentation.md`.

## Sync (DGX ↔ Surface — auto scp, never git)

After every edit, agents **must run** the correct scp script themselves (standing user permission):

| Direction | Script | Machine |
|-----------|--------|---------|
| Surface → DGX | `.\scripts\sync-to-dgx.ps1` | Surface |
| DGX → Surface | `bash scripts/sync-to-pc.sh` | DGX |
| DGX docs → Surface | `.\scripts\sync-from-dgx.ps1` | Surface |

**Agents must not** `git push`, `git pull`, `git fetch`, or touch `upstream` unless the user explicitly requests it. Publishing to GitHub is **user-only** (agent SSH key was removed after the `.env` leak).

See `.cursor/rules/agent-run-instructions.mdc` for full rules.

## Server operations on Spark

- Start/restart **3DAIGC-API** when backend config or adapters change (`scripts/run_server.sh`; requires Redis).
- After enabling a new model, verify it appears under the correct feature in `/api/v1/system/models`.

## Graphify (codebase map for Cursor)

Both repos have `.cursor/rules/graphify.mdc` and a local AST graph in `graphify-out/` (gitignored).

- **Refresh after code changes (DGX):** `bash scripts/refresh-graphify-dgx.sh` or `graphify update . --no-cluster` in each repo.
- **Refresh on Surface:** `.\scripts\refresh-graphify-surface.ps1` or `graphify update . --no-cluster` in `C:\Users\alfao\Documents\GitHub\OpenNexus3DStudio` after DGX sync.
- **Query:** `graphify query "how does X connect to Y?"` before large greps.
- **Scope:** `.graphifyignore` excludes `thirdparty/`, `node_modules/`, outputs, and huge roadmaps.
- Does **not** replace workflow rules or chat memory — only cross-file structure in the repo.

## SessionMem (cross-session memory, both machines)

- Installed globally: `npm install -g sessionmem`; registered per repo: `sessionmem install`.
- **Team mode** shared folder: `OpenNexus3DStudio/.sessionmem-team/` (gitignored). Project ID namespace: `OpenNexus3DStudio` (migrated from legacy `CharacterStudio`).
- **After coding on either machine:** run team sync **only when the user asks** — `bash scripts/sync-sessionmem-team.sh` (DGX) or `.\scripts\sync-sessionmem-team.ps1` (Surface).

## Cursor Memory Bank (tacticlaunch/cursor-bank)

- Rules: `.cursor/rules/core.mdc`, `memory-bank.mdc`
- Docs: `memory-bank/*.md` — read at task start; update with **update memory bank** after milestones.
- Commands: **PLAN** (plan only), **ACT** (implement), **update memory bank** (refresh docs).

## GitHub (no agent push access)

After the `.env` leak, the user **removed the agent SSH key from GitHub**. The agent **must not** `git push`, `git pull`, `git fetch`, merge `upstream`, or open PRs unless the user explicitly asks.

- **Commits:** only when the user explicitly asks.
- **Publishing:** user-only from Surface.
- **DGX ↔ Surface:** auto-run scp sync scripts after edits — **not** git, **not** upstream.

## Agent behavior (DGX + Surface — equal roles)

DGX and Surface agents have the **same permissions**: write project files, run local commands, SSH to the other machine, auto-run scp sync after edits. **Never** offer the user a menu of optional next steps — execute what is necessary or report a blocker. See `.cursor/rules/agent-run-instructions.mdc`.
